body.p:
The rest of the options available in the XSLT tab allow you to further
      customize the transformation scenario:

Use "xml-stylesheet" declaration - use the stylesheet declared
          with an xml-stylesheet declaration instead of the stylesheet specified in
          the XSL URL field. By default this checkbox is not selected and the
          transformation uses the XSLT stylesheet specified in the XSL URL
          field. If it is checked, the scenario is applied to the stylesheet specified explicitly in
          the XML document with the xml-stylesheet processing instruction;

